{
  "texts": [
    "Extending and diversifyingIn this technique, people modify the data to diversify the model's input data and implement it for identifying bias and modifying the model [96,121,122,129,133].",
    "One method proposes an approach to understanding a model's bias sources by adding counterfactual instances in the data points.",
    "First, they propose to modify the input data to create diversified new data points similar to the original data points but with more critical features changed.",
    "Then, the model 7 Classification of adopted methodologies to solve several types of issues Biased Training Data Inherent Bias Bias Toward Certain Feature Groups Decision Model Bias Lack of Prediction Transparency Multiple Definitions of Fairness Extending And Diversifying Adversarial Techniques Transforming Re-sampling And Relabelling Thresholding And Causal Methods Balancing Instance Distribution Incorporating Fairness Critic Implementing disparate impact Embedding Into Lower Dimension Social Cost Matrix Generalizing Fairness Definition and Metrics Discarding Protected Attribute Info Data Visualization Accuracy And Fairness Metrics Altering Model Objective Function Perturbation-based CF Generation Optimization-based Methods Rule-based Methods Combination of Techniques Multi-modal Alternative Profiles Group Fairness Causal Fairness Demographic Parity Individual Fairness Disparate Impact Equalized Odds And Calibration Contrastive Fairnessidentifies and quantifies any bias in the model by comparing the model's predictions on the original data points and the corresponding counterfactual instances [121].",
    "Another method follows this procedure, uses path-specific counterfactuals, and adjusts for bias along specific paths [129]."
  ]
}